Determines the number of AMPs to be sampled for getting row estimates of a table. 
  0 (default) - Single AMP sampling 
  2 .. 4      - Two AMP sampling 
  5           - Five AMP sampling 
  6           - Node level sampling 
  7           - All AMP sampling 
  Used only when RevertEstimationLogic == 0

Enable legacy join cardinality default when no demographics on join columns 
are available. 
  0           - Use new cardinality formulas. 
  1 (default) - Fall back to legacy formulas.

The default ratio for calculating the rows selected  in a partially covered 
interval by LIKE predicates of "abc%"- pattern. 
  Valid Range: 0 - 1 
  Default: 0.5

Determines the allowable percentage deviation between Random AMP Sample (RAS) 
and statistics histogram.  If the deviation exceeds this value, then statistics 
are assumed to be stale and are overridden by RAS. However, Histgrams are still 
used for selectivity estimations and the estimations gets extrapolated. 
  Valid Range: >= 0 
  Default: 10 
Setting this to 0 causes RAS to bypass the Histogram all the time.  Used only when 
RevertEstimationLogic == 0 and (ExtrapolateStatistics == 0 or  
ExtrapolateStatistics == 2).

Flag to revert to pre-12.0 cardinality/selectivity estimation logic 
  0           - Use new cardinality/selectivity estimation logic 
  1 (default) - Use pre-12.0 cardinality/selectivity estimation logic

Controls enabling/disabling the new constraint scan access path. 
  0           - Enable for aggregation only 
  1 (default) - Disable. 
  2           - Enable for aggregation and retrieval (not available yet) 
  Used only when RevertEstimationLogic == 0

Determines the action to be taken if optimizer sanity checks of demographic or costing 
information fails: 
  0           - Quiet mode.  Fall back to default demographic or cost value. 
  1           - Parser crash with snapshot dump. 
  2 (default) - Log occurance in the event log and fall back to default value. 
  3           - First 2 occurances, generate a snapshot dump and log all occurance 
                in the event log and fall back to default value.

If the uniqueness of a column is more that this percent, it is assumed to be 
a rolling column and gets qualified for distinct values or rows extrapolation if 
the statistics are determined to be stale. 
  Valid Range: 0 - 100 
  Default: 95 
Setting this to 0 disables extrapolations.  Used only when RevertEstimationLogic == 0 
and (ExtrapolateStatistics == 0 or ExtrapolateStatistics == 2).

Maximum number of statistics intervals that are allowed. 
  Valid Range: 1 - 240 
  Default: 100

Flag to enable/disable extrapolating demographics such as unique values or 
rows when stale statistics are detected. 
  0           - Enable extrapolation 
  1 (default) - Disable extrapolation 
  2           - Enable extrapolation by honoring single-Amp sampling all the time. 
  10          - Enable unconditional extrapolation

If a table has a single row access via a UPI or USI, this flag determines whether 
or not the optimizer can retrieve this row to derive more accurate estimates. 
  0  (default) - Disable this optimization. 
  1            - Enable this optimization. 
  Used only when RevertEstimationLogic == 0

Flag to determine whether or not to allow session level derived statistics for 
global and volatile tables. 
  0  (default) - Disallow session level derived statistics. 
  1            - Enable these derived statistics. 
  Used only when RevertEstimationLogic == 0

When no statistics are available on a NUPI, this is the assumed uniqueness. 
  Valid Range: 50 - 100 
  Default: 75 
  Used only when RevertEstimationLogic == 0

Enables or disables join cardinality adjustment based on skew. 
  0 (default) - Disable adjustment. 
  1           - Enable adjustment.

Determines the allowable absolute deviation of rows between Random AMP Sample (RAS) 
and statistics histogram.  If the deviation exceeds this value, then statistics 
are assumed to be stale and are overridden by RAS. However, Histgrams are still 
used for selectivity estimations and the estimations gets extrapolated. 
  Valid Range: >= 0 
  Default: 10,000 rows 
Setting this to 0 causes disables this check.  Used only when  
RevertEstimationLogic == 0 and (ExtrapolateStatistics == 0 or 
ExtrapolateStatistics == 2).

The value of '0' enables PGB with costing.
The value of '1' enables PGB (partial SUM) without costing.
The value of '2' disables PGB.
The value of '3' disables PGB for PPI tables.
The value of '4' enables PGB (SORT/GROUP) without costing.
The default value is 0.

This flag is used to set the fudge factor
used in the optimizer. Default is 0. A Value 0 means use
the default fudge factor of 75%.0

HTMemAlloc - This field specifies the percentage of memory to be
allocated to a hash table for a hash join.  A value of 0 turns off
hash joins. Valid range is 0 to 10.
The default value is 10.
The base in megabytes to which the\nHTMemAlloc percentage is applied. The valid range is\n1-1024, with 20 being the default value

DisableDPE  - This flag is used to control dynamic
partition elimination (DPE). By default, this value is 0.
0 = Allow all DPE (default).
1 = Disable product join DPE.
2 = Disable merge join DPE.
3 = Disable both product and merge join DPE.
4 = Disable product join DPE for multilevel PPI tables.
    Both product and merge join DPE are enabled for single-
    level PPI tables.
5 = Disable product join DPE for multilevel PPI tables
   and disable DPE for merge join. Product join DPE for
    single-level PPI tables is enabled.

This flag is used to control the
 white tree validation process. By default, this value is 0.0 = Validate White Tree and die if found problem in final plan (Default).
1 = Validate White Tree and report warning if found problem.
2 = Validate White Tree and auto correct if found problem.
3 = Disable White Tree Validation.
4 = Validate White Tree and die if found problem in intermediate/final plan
    (Not recommended in customer side).

This integer determines whether Sliding window
merge joins are applicable for PPI tables.
By default the value is 0.
0 = All sliding window joins are enabled.
1 = Basic sliding window joins are disabled
2 = All sliding window joins are disabled

Set a threshold for the number
of connections among the tables to be joined above
which 2 or more lookahead will be disabled. The threshold
is set as an integer among 0 .. 100 as follows:
      NLookAheadControl = 100 - a*100/b
Here, a is the maximal number of connections allowed for 2
or more lookahead; b is the maxmial number of possible
connections, currently b=2016. The default value for
NLookAheadControl is 0, which means always enable 2 or
more lookahead.

This field enables or disables
1) the performance enhancements associated with
  eliminating rowids at the secondary index level
  if there is a residual condition on the partitioning
  column, for a PPI table and
 2) SingleAMP NUSI access, if NUSI index is on the same
   column(s) as NUPI.
A value of 0 enables both the optimization.
A value of 1 disables the eliminating the rowids at the
 index level optimization.
A value of 2 disables the single amp NUSI optimization.
 A value of 3 disables both the optimizations.
The default is 0.

Maximum number of blocks that can be assumed to be in cache when the 
same set of blocks is reread during a join.
  Value Range: >= 0 
  Default: 10

Condition costing control levels. Values are IN (1, 2, 3) where: 
   1 (default) - New condition costing and ordering  
  2           - New condition costing but ordering disabled  
  3           - Disable new condition costing and ordering

Determines the number of AMPs to be sampled for getting row estimates of a table. 
  0 (default) - Single AMP sampling 
  2 .. 4      - Two AMP sampling 
  5           - Five AMP sampling 
  6           - Node level sampling 
  7           - All AMP sampling 
  Used only when RevertEstimationLogic == 0

Enable legacy join cardinality default when no demographics on join columns 
are available. 
  0 (default) - Use new cardinality formulas. 
  1           - Fall back to legacy formulas.

The default ratio for calculating the rows selected  in a partially covered 
interval by LIKE predicates of "abc%"- pattern. 
  Valid Range: 0 - 1 
  Default: 0.125

Determines the allowable percentage deviation between Random AMP Sample (RAS) 
and statistics histogram.  If the deviation exceeds this value, then statistics 
are assumed to be stale and are overridden by RAS. However, Histgrams are still 
used for selectivity estimations and the estimations gets extrapolated. 
  Valid Range: >= 0 
  Default: 10 
Setting this to 0 causes RAS to bypass the Histogram all the time.  Used only when 
RevertEstimationLogic == 0 and (ExtrapolateStatistics == 0 or 
ExtrapolateStatistics == 2).

Flag to revert to pre-12.0 cardinality/selectivity estimation logic 
  0 (default) - Use new cardinality/selectivity estimation logic 
  1           - Use pre-12.0 cardinality/selectivity estimation logic
Revert to prior release skew-based cardinality adjustments \nCurrently unused; subsumed by RevertEstimationLogic. \n

Controls enabling/disabling the new constraint scan access path. 
  0 (default) - Enable for aggregation only 
  1           - Disable. 
  2           - Enable for aggregation and retrieval (not available yet) 
  Used only when RevertEstimationLogic == 0

Determines the action to be taken if optimizer sanity checks of demographic or costing 
information fails: 
  0           - Quiet mode.  Fall back to default demographic or cost value. 
  1           - Parser crash with snapshot dump. 
  2 (default) - Log occurance in the event log and fall back to default value. 
  3           - First 2 occurances, generate a snapshot dump and log all occurance 
                in the event log and fall back to default value.

If the uniqueness of a column is more that this percent, it is assumed to be 
a rolling column and gets qualified for distinct values or rows extrapolation if 
the statistics are determined to be stale. 
  Valid Range: 0 - 100 
  Default: 95 
Setting this to 0 disables extrapolations.  Used only when RevertEstimationLogic == 0 
and (ExtrapolateStatistics == 0 or ExtrapolateStatistics == 2).

Enables/Disables Type 2 pre-join costing logic.  When enabled, cost estimates 
are made for any additional steps required on the input relations prior to the 
join, for example, sort/duplicate elimination, aggregation, and so on. 
  0           - Disable completely 
  1 (default) - Enable for both uniq-id and non-uniq-id join planning paths. 
  2           - Enable only for the uniq-id path.

Maximum number of statistics intervals that are allowed. 
  Valid Range: 1 - 240 
  Default: 200

Flag to enable/disable extrapolating demographics such as unique values or 
rows when stale statistics are detected. 
  0 (default) - Enable extrapolation 
  1           - Disable extrapolation 
  2           - Enable extrapolation by honoring single-Amp sampling always

If a table has a single row access via a UPI or USI, this flag determines whether 
or not the optimizer can retrieve this row to derive more accurate estimates. 
  0           - Disable this optimization. 
  1 (default) - Enable this optimization. 
  Used only when RevertEstimationLogic == 0

Flag to determine whether or not to allow session level derived statistics for 
global and volatile tables. 
  0           - Disallow session level derived statistics. 
  1 (default) - Enable these derived statistics. 
  Used only when RevertEstimationLogic == 0

When no statistics are available on a NUPI, this is the assumed uniqueness.

Determines the allowable absolute deviation of rows between Random AMP Sample (RAS) 
and statistics histogram.  If the deviation exceeds this value, then statistics

HTMemAlloc - This field specifies the percentage of memory to be
allocated to a hash table for a hash join.  A value of 0 turns off
hash joins. Valid range is 0 to 10.
The default value is 10.
The base in megabytes to which the\nHTMemAlloc percentage is applied. The valid range is\n1-1024, with 20 being the default value

DisableDPE  - This flag is used to control dynamic
partition elimination (DPE). By default, this value is 0.
0 = Allow all DPE (default).
1 = Disable product join DPE.
2 = Disable merge join DPE.
3 = Disable both product and merge join DPE.
4 = Disable product join DPE for multilevel PPI tables.
    Both product and merge join DPE are enabled for single-
    level PPI tables.
5 = Disable product join DPE for multilevel PPI tables
   and disable DPE for merge join. Product join DPE for
    single-level PPI tables is enabled.

This flag is used to control the
 white tree validation process. By default, this value is 0.0 = Validate White Tree and die if found problem in final plan (Default).
1 = Validate White Tree and report warning if found problem.
2 = Validate White Tree and auto correct if found problem.
3 = Disable White Tree Validation.
4 = Validate White Tree and die if found problem in intermediate/final plan
    (Not recommended in customer side).

This integer determines whether Sliding window
merge joins are applicable for PPI tables.
By default the value is 0.
0 = All sliding window joins are enabled.
1 = Basic sliding window joins are disabled
2 = All sliding window joins are disabled

Set a threshold for the number
of connections among the tables to be joined above
which 2 or more lookahead will be disabled. The threshold
is set as an integer among 0 .. 100 as follows:
      NLookAheadControl = 100 - a*100/b
Here, a is the maximal number of connections allowed for 2
or more lookahead; b is the maxmial number of possible
connections, currently b=2016. The default value for
NLookAheadControl is 0, which means always enable 2 or
more lookahead.

Used to override the number of available write column-partition

context. The allowed range is 1 - 16 which represents a multiple of

  CPMerge is reading a column partition from the CP merge spool

  as the number of data blocks that are read before deleting those
  data blocks when CPMerge is reading a column partition from the 
  CP merge spool.
The default is not to be set(-1).

If not set, 1000 is used as the number of data blocks
  that are read before deleting those data blocks when

  an altered version of the column-partition with an available
  column partition number.
If it is set to 0, data blocks that are read are not deleted 
  when reading a column partition until completely finishing 
  the read of the column partition.
If it is set to a value between 1 or higher, this value is used 
  as the number of data blocks that are read before deleting 
  those data blocks when ALTER TABLE is reading a column partition 
  in order to write an altered version of the column-partition with
  an available column partition number.
The default is not to be set(-1).

AutoCompress has an integer value.  The value must be between 0 and 2. 
If it is 3 or not set, autocompression is optimized for both CPU and disk I/O.   
0 indicates no autocompression.  1 indicates autocompression is optimized only for disk I/O.  
Default Not set.

AutoCompressUTF8SampleP defines the percentage of column partition values to  
sample in a container to determine if UTF8 compression is to be used for the container. 
AutoCompressUTF8SampleP has an integer value.  The value must be between 0 and 100.   
If it is 0 or not set, 5 (indicating 5%) will be  used. Default Not set.

AutoCompressDynamicVLP defines the percentage of local value-list dictionary entries  
used to determine the number of column partition values allowed in the CPValues list 
(dynamic value-list dictionary) when using local value-list compression  
Note that this is capped by AutoCompressDynamicVLMax.AutoCompressDynamicVLP has an integer value.  
The value must be greater than or equal to 0.  If it is 0 or not set, 10 will be used. 
Default Not set.

AutoCompressDynamicVLMax defines the absolute maximum number of column partition values 
allowed in the CPValues list (dynamic value-list dictionary) when using local value-list compression. 
AutoCompressDynamicVLMax has an integer value.  The value must be greater than or equal to 0.   
If it is 0 or not set, 100 will be used. Default Not set.

AutoCRMin defines the minimum compression ratio needed by an autocompression technique  
for it to be considered for a container when it is being autocompressed. 
AutoCRMin has an integer value.  The value must be between 0 and 100.   
If it is 0 or not set, 25 will be used. Default Not set.

Following are the Compression Techniques Categories: 
1. Direct on AC Bits & CP Values 
2. Direct on AC Bits & Sequential on CP Values 
3. Sequential on AC Bits & Direct on CP Values 
4. Sequential on AC Bits & CP Values. 
AutoCRDelta1 defines the delta for category 1 autocompression techniques over category  
2, 3, and 4 autocompression techniques.AutoCRDelta1 has an integer value.  The value must be  
between 0 and 100.  If it is 0 or not set, 25 (indicating 25%) will be used. Default Not set.

AutoCRDelta2 defines the delta for category 2 autocompression techniques over the other  
category 3 and 4 autocompression techniques.AutoCRDelta2 has an integer value.  The value must be  
between 0 and 100.  If it is 0 or not set, 10 (indicating 10%) will be used. Default Not set.

AutoCRDelta3 defines the delta for category 3 autocompression techniques over the category 4  
autocompression techniques.AutoCRDelta3 has an integer value.  The value must be between  
0 and 100.  If it is 0 or not set, 10 (indicating 10%) will be used. Default Not set.

DeleteCPCR defines the minimum compression ratio for a recompressed container of the delete column 
partition over the previous compressed copy of the container; if the recompressed container does 
meet this minimum, the previous compressed copy of the container is retained.DeleteCPCR has an 
integer value.  The value must be between 0 and 100.  If it is 0 or not set, 10 (indicating 10%) 
will be used. Default Not set.

DeleteCPIncrP defines the percentage increase for a container's BR compression 4th argument 
(3-byte unsigned integer) y that occurs when the container is recompressed.  When the number of 
1 bits set in a container exceeds the current value of y, the container is recompressed and y is  
increased; that is, y is replaced by the maximum of CEILING(y* (1+DeleteCPIncrP/100)) and 2^24-1.  
The container is a container in the delete column partition.DeleteCPIncrP has an integer value.  
The value must be greater than or equal to zero.  If it is 0 or not set, 25 (indicating 25%)  
will be used. Default Not set.
